quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Ah! knoweth he not, that when that which is in the graves shall be laid bare"
  100,10,And that which is in men's breasts shall be brought forth
  100,11,Verily their Lord shall on that day be informed concerning them
  101,1,THE BLOW
  101,2,what is the Blow
  101,3,Who shall teach thee what the Blow is
  101,4,The Day when men shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains shall be like flocks of carded wool
  101,6,Then as to him whose balances are heavy
  101,7,his shall be a life that shall please him well
  101,8,And as to him whose balances are light
  101,9,his dwelling-place shall be the pit
  101,10,And who shall teach thee what the pit (El-Hawiya) is
  101,11,A raging fire
  102,1,THE DESIRE of increasing riches occupieth you
  102,2,Till ye come to the grave
  102,3,Nay! but in the end ye shall know
  102,4,"Nay! once more,in the end ye shall know your folly"
  102,5,Nay! would that ye knew it with knowledge of certainty
  102,6,Surely ye shall see hell-fire
  102,7,Then shall ye surely see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,Then shall ye on that day be taken to task concerning pleasures
  103,1,I SWEAR by the declining day
  103,2,"Verily, man's lot is cast amid destruction"
  103,3,"Save those who believe and do the things which be right, and enjoin truth and enjoin stedfastness on each other"
  104,1,"Woe to every BACKBITER, Defamer"
  104,2,Who amasseth wealth and storeth it against the future
  104,3,He thinketh surely that his wealth shall be with him for ever
  104,4,Nay! for verily he shall be flung into the Crushing Fire
  104,5,And who shall teach thee what the Crushing Fire is
  104,6,It is God's kindled fire
  104,7,Which shall mount above the hearts of the damned
  104,8,It shall verily rise over them like a vault
  104,9,On outstretched columns
  105,1,HAST thou not seen how thy Lord dealt with the army of the ELEPHANT
  105,2,Did he not cause their stratagem to miscarry
  105,3,And he sent against them birds in flocks (ababils)
  105,4,Claystones did they hurl down upon them
  105,5,And he made them like stubble eaten down
  106,1,For the union of the KOREISCH
  106,2,Their union in equipping caravans winter and summer
  106,3,"And let them worship the Lord of this house, who hath provided them with food against hunger"
  106,4,And secured them against alarm
  107,1,WHAT thinkest thou of him who treateth our RELIGION as a lie
  107,2,He it is who trusteth away the orphan
  107,3,And stirreth not others up to feed the poor
  107,4,Woe to those who pray
  107,5,But in their prayer are careless
  107,6,Who make a shew of devotion
  107,7,But refuse help to the needy
  108,1,TRULY we have given thee an ABUNDANCE
  108,2,"Pray therefore to the Lord, and slay the victims"
  108,3,Verily whose hateth thee shall be childless
  109,1,"SAY: O ye UNBELIEVERS"
  109,2,I worship not that which ye worship
  109,3,And ye do not worship that which I worship
  109,4,I shall never worship that which ye worship
  109,5,Neither will ye worship that which I worship
  109,6,To you be your religion; to me my religion
  110,1,WHEN the HELP of God and the victory arrive
  110,2,And thou seest men entering the religion of God by troops
  110,3,"Then utter the praise of thy Lord, implore His pardon; for He loveth to turn in mercy"
  111,1,"LET the hands of ABU LAHAB perish,and let himself perish"
  111,2,His wealth and his gains shall avail him not
  111,3,Burned shall he be at the fiery flame
  111,4,And his wife laden with fire wood
  111,5,On her neck a rope of palm fibre
  112,1,"SAY: He is God alone"
  112,2,God the eternal
  112,3,"He begetteth not, and He is not begotten"
  112,4,And there is none like unto Him
  113,1,"SAY: I betake me for refuge to the Lord of the DAY BREAK"
  113,2,Against the mischiefs of his creation
  113,3,And against the mischief of the night when it overtaketh me
  113,4,And against the mischief of weird women
  113,5,And against the mischief of the envier when he envieth
  114,1,"SAY: I betake me for refuge to the Lord of MEN"
  114,2,The King of men
  114,3,The God of men
  114,4,Against the mischief of the stealthily withdrawing whisperer
  114,5,Who whispereth in man's breast
  114,6,Against djinn and men